---
import Page from '@/layouts/Page.astro'
import { SITE } from '@/lib/site'

export const prerender = true

const lastUpdated = '9 May 2026'
---

<Page
  title="Terms"
  description="Plain-English terms for trominal.app and the public demo backend."
  active="terms"
>
  <header class="page-head">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>Terms</span>
      <h1>Terms of use.</h1>
      <p class="lede">Plain English. No surprise clauses. Last updated {lastUpdated}.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section flush">
    <div class="wrap">
      <article class="prose" style="max-width:760px">
        <p>
          These terms cover the website at <strong>{SITE.domain}</strong> and the public demo
          backend at <strong>{new URL(SITE.demo.backendUrl).host}</strong>. Trominal the
          software — the source code at <a href={SITE.github.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener"
            >github.com/{SITE.github.owner}/{SITE.github.repo}</a> — is licensed under
          AGPL-3.0; the license text is the source of truth for source-code rights and
          obligations.
        </p>

        <h2>1. The software</h2>
        <p>
          Trominal is published under the <a href="/license">GNU Affero General Public License
          v3.0</a>. You may use, modify, and redistribute it under those terms — including
          running modified versions, provided you make the modified source available to users
          who interact with it over a network.
        </p>
        <p>
          The software is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. To the extent
          permitted by law, the maintainers and contributors are not liable for any damages
          arising from its use.
        </p>

        <h2>2. The demo backend</h2>

        <h3>What the demo is</h3>
        <p>
          <code>{SITE.demo.backendUrl}</code> is a public Trominal instance we host so you can
          try the product without setting up your own server. It is a <strong>real, hardened
          instance</strong> with TLS, rate limiting, and 2FA available. It is also
          <strong>ephemeral</strong>: the database is wiped periodically without notice.
        </p>

        <h3>What you may use the demo for</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Evaluating Trominal end-to-end with one or two devices</li>
          <li>Testing connection sharing, snippets, and identity workflows</li>
          <li>Smoke-testing the desktop and web builds against a remote backend</li>
          <li>Pointing your client at a known-good server while developing locally</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What you may not use the demo for</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Production workloads, customer data, or anything you can't afford to lose</li>
          <li>Automated load testing, scraping, or bulk imports</li>
          <li>Hosting content that violates third-party rights or applicable law</li>
          <li>Attempts to defeat rate limiting, bypass authentication, or deny service to other users</li>
          <li>Anything illegal under the laws of your jurisdiction or ours</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to suspend or delete demo accounts that breach these terms,
          without warning. We also reserve the right to take the demo offline, change its
          terms, or reset its database — at any time, for any reason.
        </p>

        <h3>No SLA, no guarantees</h3>
        <p>
          The demo has no uptime guarantee, no support SLA, no data-recovery promise, and no
          warranty. If you need any of those things, self-host.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Reporting abuse and security issues</h2>
        <p>
          If you believe someone is abusing the demo backend, or if you've found a security
          vulnerability in Trominal, email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}
            >{SITE.contactEmail}</a>. Don't open public issues for security problems — the
          coordinated-disclosure process is documented in <a href="/security">SECURITY.md</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Trademark</h2>
        <p>
          "Trominal" and the Trominal logo are unregistered marks of the project. Forks and
          derivatives that change behavior in ways users would not expect from upstream should
          rename and re-brand to avoid confusion. See <a href="/brand">the brand kit</a> for
          guidance.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p>
          When these terms change, the date at the top updates and the diff lands in the
          public repo. No silent edits.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Governing law and contact</h2>
        <p>
          The Trominal project is community-run; there is no parent corporation behind it.
          For legal questions about the marketing site or the demo backend, email
          <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Page>
